INSERT INTO monumento (nombreMon, idioma, descMon) VALUES ('lapuente', 'en', 'La Puente is a small suburb created due to the course of the Alberca stream (Arrolberca) through the village. Here there is a beautiful stone bridge from where we can admire the church tower in the background. In times of low rainfall you can go down to the stream and contemplate the landscape from the stones below. On the other hand, in rainy or thawing seasons, such as spring, we can see how the abundant flow of crystal-clear water of the Alberca stream runs through here.');
INSERT INTO monumento (nombreMon, idioma, descMon) VALUES ('barrioelcastillo', 'en', 'The district of El Castillo is the oldest district of the town, where the first foundation of what we know today as La Alberca took place. Although nowadays there is practically no evidence of its existence, the languages of La Alberca tell that in the time of the Arabs and Visigoths there was a fort with a bell tower that served as a watchtower to keep watch over the arrival of enemies to the town. It is also said that the houses that were built on stones served as a natural defensive wall.');
INSERT INTO monumento (nombreMon, idioma, descMon) VALUES ('ermitadelhumilladero', 'en', 'Most of the villages in this region of Salamanca have a hermitage of the Humilladero. This used to be the site of the boundary cross and was a place for visitors to say goodbye and pray when leaving on their journey or on their arrival. In other times it was a place of entry for those who came from other distant lands, for the pursuits of life and the affairs of cities.');
INSERT INTO monumento (nombreMon, idioma, descMon) VALUES ('ermitadelhumilladero', 'en', 'The hermitage of El Humilladero in La Alberca, also known as the hermitage of La Vera Cruz or "El Millaero", is a solidly built hermitage dating from 1678 with a fine wooden portico with granite columns and a staircase along the entire façade.');
INSERT INTO monumento (nombreMon, idioma, descMon) VALUES ('ermitadelhumilladero', 'en', 'Its front is a curious framework of wooden windows that can be opened with the utmost care and respect to be able to look inside. This hermitage, which predates that of San Antonio, houses the Santo Cristo de la Misericordia (Holy Christ of Mercy), which on Holy Thursday joins the general procession that comes from the village to march together towards the church.');
