INSERT INTO monumento (categoriaMon, nombreMon, idioma, descMon) VALUES ('plazaiglesia', 'marranosananton', 'en', 'The figure of the Marrano de San Antón is very important in La Alberca. Such is the devotion that the inhabitants of La Alberca decided to pay tribute to him by installing a monument to the Marrano de San Antón on the Solano Cimero, next to the Parish Church, which recalls a tradition that goes back more than five centuries. Installed in August 1996, the granite sculpture was made by the Escuela Taller del INEM Sierra de Francia, with the collaboration of the Diputación de Salamanca and the European Social Fund.');
INSERT INTO monumento (categoriaMon, nombreMon, idioma, descMon) VALUES ('plazaiglesia', 'predios', 'en', 'In La Alberca, specifically in the vicinity of the parish church, there are some small stones that at first sight look like a boat placed vertically to be used as a stage prop. However, their significance does not lie there, as their carved design on the stone reveals. They are known as praedium, a word derived from the Latin: Prae (before) and aedes (temple).');
INSERT INTO monumento (categoriaMon, nombreMon, idioma, descMon) VALUES ('plazaiglesia', 'predios', 'en', 'The predium is a property of a certain surface area, a plot of land enclosed for burials. In the past, in most Spanish villages, the deceased were buried inside the churches. The predium was commissioned to stonemasons to delimit the land owned by the church so that, if there was no more room to bury the deceased in the church, it would serve as a place of eternal rest.');
INSERT INTO monumento (categoriaMon, nombreMon, idioma, descMon) VALUES ('plazaiglesia', 'predios', 'en', 'Over the years, the collapse of the cemetery of the church, and its surroundings and the idea of creating new enclosures outside the village led to the opening of the cemetery of the Ermita de San Blas and later, as it was too small and so close to inhabited areas, what is now the village cemetery was built in the area of La Somá, on the outskirts of the village.');
