INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, descrArte) VALUES ('inicio','en','On the other hand, the Serrano embroidery stands out, with images of floral bouquets or mythological animals, fish and birds, together with other religious motifs, which differentiate them from those made in other regions.');
INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, descrArte) VALUES ('bordado','en','Serrano embroidery was used in textiles for the home, in popular clothing or in ritual cloths and altar cloths, among other things. The animals, mythological or real (griffins and dragons and the occasional cockerel, butterfly, wild boar, owl or dog), are interwoven with plants, including the tree of life.');
INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, descrArte) VALUES ('bordado','en','Each animal represented has a meaning, for example, the two-headed eagle represents marriage; the lion, virility; the one-headed bird, womanhood; the heart from which the flower emerges, love; the tree of life, health and longevity, and so on.');
INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, descrArte) VALUES ('bordado','en','Other features of Serrano embroidery are the absence of human figures and geometric motifs, suggesting the influence of ancient oriental, Renaissance and Moorish civilisations. Another interesting fact is the language of the colours used: blue was used to shroud the deceased, while red was embroidered on the bedclothes of newlyweds. In the mid-20th century, new colours were incorporated: mauve, purple, grass green, cobalt blue, salmon, among others.');
INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, descrArte) VALUES ('bordado','en','The basic materials for embroidery were linen and wool. Over the years, these were replaced by silk thread, and later came cotton which, together with silk, has survived to the present day. Until the 19th century, handlooms were used to weave the fabrics, using the mixed technique of counted and drawn threads. Once they disappeared, industrial weaving with other fibres began to be used.');
INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, nombreTraje, descrArte) VALUES ('trajes','en','vistas','The vistas suit is perhaps the most interesting and richest in Spain, as well as being the oldest. It is difficult to determine the date of its origin, as even in the village there is no one who knows its origins, although some old women claim that it is of Jewish origin. It is of absolute chastity, as it hides the anatomy of women and conceals her forms. It was originally a wedding dress, but over time it has lost its bridal character to become a festive garment linked to the celebration of processions and offertories.');
INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, nombreTraje, descrArte) VALUES ('trajes','en','vistas','The most unique feature of the Traje de Vistas is undoubtedly its jewellery. The ensemble is mainly made of coral and silver, including reliquaries, patens, medals, crucifixes and all kinds of jewellery, weighing around 10 kilos. This jewellery is loaded with religious symbolism and elements of protection against evil, misfortune or illness.');
INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, nombreTraje, descrArte) VALUES ('trajes','en','vistas','This suit from La Alberca has inspired artists, painters such as Sorolla, sculptors and photographers such as Ortiz Echagüe, who portrays the women of La Alberca in all their splendour. The great masters such as Givenchy and Galiano have also drunk from this source of the mountain village, because the richness of its forms, the superimposition of fabrics and jewels and the singular way in which it sits on the body of women body suggest a multitude of ideas.');
INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, nombreTraje, descrArte) VALUES ('trajes','en','ventioseno','The ventioseno is the authentic suit of respect, proper for ceremonies of gravity, for mourning and for going to the temple. It consists of a black cloak, with a blue waistcoat; white or coloured cotton stockings, preferably red; a small scarf on the chest and a severe blanket on top. Everything is austere and grave.');
