INSERT INTO otroslugares (categoriaOtros, idioma, nombreOtro, descrOtro) VALUES ('peñadefrancia','en','naveizquierda','In the chapel of San Andrew, the light enters through a stained glass window of three sections, with a single colour predominating in each of them. The one in the centre shows a green cross, a symbol of hope for all Christians and an allusion to the martyrdom to which the apostle was subjected. The tendency to place the colour blue in the upper part is indicative of heaven, the place of divinity.');
INSERT INTO otroslugares (categoriaOtros, idioma, nombreOtro, descrOtro) VALUES ('peñadefrancia','en','naveizquierda','Finally, in the Chapel of Christ we find another stained glass window with three sections: the first, in the upper part, depicts the face of Christ, maintaining the harmony of the three colours in the composition. The central part shows two crosses, one in red and the other in green. The green cross is a symbol of hope. Christ saves us, gives us hope, by dying on the cross. The red cross: symbol of blood, pain and sacrifice. The lower part of the stained glass window is thought to allude to the words of the prophet Jeremiah "I will raise up for David a Branch of righteousness". (Jer 33:15).');
