INSERT INTO otroslugares (categoriaOtros, idioma, nombreOtro, descrOtro) VALUES ('peñadefrancia','en','elsaltodelniño','The name of El Salto del Niño alludes to an event that has been repeated throughout the history of the sanctuary: a child playing among the rocks slipped and fell into the depths of one of the ravines. When his parents, thinking to find him lifeless, descended into the depths of the chasm, they found the child sitting and playing. The family members, witnesses to these events, interpreted what happened as a special favour from the Virgen de la Peña.');
INSERT INTO otroslugares (categoriaOtros, idioma, nombreOtro, descrOtro) VALUES ('peñadefrancia','en','lacasabaja','La Casa Baja was a monastery, declared a National Historic and Artistic Monument in 1956, built to serve as a winter home for the Dominicans of La Peña de Francia. In addition, the monastery also served as a place of study for the friars and as a larder for the Peña during the months when it was not inhabited. Its name was given as La Casa Baja (The Lower House) because the convent on the cliff was known as La Casa Alta (The Upper House).');
INSERT INTO otroslugares (categoriaOtros, idioma, nombreOtro, descrOtro) VALUES ('peñadefrancia','en','lacasabaja','When in 1436 King John II entrusted the sanctuary of La Peña to the Dominican friars, the king, in the same document, also ordered that in love of Our Lady a house should be founded on the summit of La Peña, in a place that was habitable, or at the foot of the mountain range, if in winter it was not habitable due to the altitude. Two years earlier, Simón Vela, who had built the first chapel for the Virgin on the highest crag of the Peña, also built a small house on the slope of the mountain facing south, where he could spend the winter.');
INSERT INTO otroslugares (categoriaOtros, idioma, nombreOtro, descrOtro) VALUES ('peñadefrancia','en','lacasabaja','Initially, La Casa Baja was built to the north of El Maíllo, on the road to La Puebla, in what had previously been a mill. It was a small, damp, poor house in an unhealthy location. The Dominican monks lived there for forty years. However, the building that today is known as La Casa Baja is located to the south of El Maíllo. Its first stone was laid on 18 August 1516. It had a small chestnut wood with two fountains, two ponds and a vegetable garden.');
INSERT INTO otroslugares (categoriaOtros, idioma, nombreOtro, descrOtro) VALUES ('peñadefrancia','en','lacasabaja','The friars lived in the lower house from November to May, specifically from All Souls Day (1st November) until the Wednesday before Corpus Christi (end of May-beginning of June) to prepare for the feast of Pentecost, one of the four most important feasts in La Peña. However, a small group of religious remained at the Risco to attend to the pilgrims and the worship of the Sanctuary.');
INSERT INTO otroslugares (categoriaOtros, idioma, nombreOtro, descrOtro) VALUES ('peñadefrancia','en','lacasabaja','In the 19th century, the War of Independence left all the buildings with traces of looting and destruction. Despite this, in 1816 the monks began the restoration of the convent. This tenacity in building and rebuilding the convent was put an end to in 1835 by the Disentailment of Mendizábal.');
INSERT INTO otroslugares (categoriaOtros, idioma, nombreOtro, descrOtro) VALUES ('peñadefrancia','en','lacasabaja','When the monks were expelled and the convent was sold, the destruction of the convent began. Today, there are no more roofs, the lodge of the porter, the ashlar cloister, the refectory, the kitchen, the cells, the bakery, the offices... everything is full of brambles and weeds that grow luxuriantly on the floor and walls. There are still traces of what was once a royal staircase, of a large and beautiful neoclassical church that serves as a hayloft and stable, and the only remaining vaults of the monastery, in what were once the sacristy and the chapter house, threaten to fall down.');       
