INSERT INTO otroslugares (categoriaOtros, idioma, nombreOtro, descrOtro) VALUES ('batuecas','en','pinturas','In the heart of the valley and along the course of the Batuecas river there are up to 15 rock shelters where the best collection of schematic paintings in Salamanca can be found. The cave paintings of Batuecas are a true monument of prehistory, providing it with curious and interesting data, because although in themselves and in themselves they are simple, and without the complications observed in the Cantabrian-Asturian caves or those of Levante, those of Batuecas are of a special type and establish a period of the life of "wild man" in primitive times, corresponding to the beginning of the Neolithic period.');
INSERT INTO otroslugares (categoriaOtros, idioma, nombreOtro, descrOtro) VALUES ('batuecas','en','pinturas','Although all of them are of interest, the main ones are known as "Las cabras pintadas", "Cueva del Cristo", "Umbría del Cristo", "Las Torres", "Canchal del Águila", "Zarzalón" and "Risco del Ciervo", all of them curious, interesting and worthy of being visited by lovers of prehistory.  In them, the images reproduce animal and human figures in colours such as ochre, pink, black, yellow and white.');
INSERT INTO otroslugares (categoriaOtros, idioma, nombreOtro, descrOtro) VALUES ('batuecas','en','pinturas','Among the many shelters with cave paintings, the one commonly known as "Las cabras pintás" (The Painted Goats) stands out. There are representations of numerous mountain goats, some in red and others in brownish red. Some are covered with an elongated squarish sign. Others, in white, are superimposed on representations, stripes and dots in brighter tones. Finally, they appear, also in black, in small numbers and accompanied by a sign of the same colour. The fish, drawn in white, are in the lower part and offer details of undoubted interest.');
INSERT INTO otroslugares (categoriaOtros, idioma, nombreOtro, descrOtro) VALUES ('batuecas','en','pinturas','At the time of their discovery, the paintings of Las Batuecas, like the other prehistoric paintings in Spain, gave rise to long and numerous doubts as to their authenticity, which was denied by foreign scholars. Nowadays it is beyond doubt, it has been admitted by all and demonstrated to satiety, that they were made by men of the Stone Age, since the most modern paintings date back several thousand years.');
INSERT INTO otroslugares (categoriaOtros, idioma, nombreOtro, descrOtro) VALUES ('batuecas','en','pinturas','Proof of their authenticity can be found in the fact that they are sometimes in caves that have been opened by chance, since the entrance is one that has been blocked, either by calcareous deposits or by other natural phenomena. In addition, paintings have been found covered by the accumulation of archaeological remains. It can also be seen that paintings from the same period are of the same style and technique, even though they are hundreds of kilometres apart, repeating the same signs and figures.');
