INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'santaagueda', 'This tradition has its roots in medieval times, when the women of La Alberca gathered to protect the town from invaders. Today, the Fiesta de Santa Águeda is an opportunity to celebrate gender equality and participation of women in public life, as well as to honour the memory of Santa Águeda, one of the most venerated saints in the region.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'semanasanta', 'Holy Week in La Alberca begins on Palm Sunday with the blessing of the branches in the Plaza Mayor of the village. Apart from Palm Sunday, the most important days are Maundy Thursday and Good Friday. If you visit La Alberca on Maundy Thursday, you can witness the theatrical performance of the "Passion of Christ" by Cateja Teatro in the atrium of the church at dusk.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'semanasanta', 'Good Friday is the most eagerly awaited day, when most of the most significant events of the festivities take place and most of the processions take place. The day begins with a Stations of the Cross that take place through the streets of the town. In the afternoon, the procession of the Holy Burial takes place. The Juita or Judas Iscariot, who holds the image of Jesus carrying the Cross with a rope, stands out in this procession.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'semanasanta', 'Also the procession of the Virgen de los Dolores, an image of great solemnity and devotion that is kept in the chapel of Dolores in the Parish Church. From 10 p.m. onwards, the procession of the Virgen de los Dolores takes place. The peculiarity of this procession is that it is carried out completely in silence. On Holy Saturday, at 12 p.m. in the Plaza Mayor, the Encounter of the Virgen de la Asunción, Patron Saint of La Alberca, with the "Alleluia", a representation of the Risen Jesus Christ, takes place.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'lunesdepascua', 'On Easter Monday, the festivity known as Día del Pendón (Day of the Banner) is celebrated, commemorating the battle of Las Matancias. The banner is placed on the balcony of the Town Hall in the morning and at midday the quintos come to the Plaza Mayor dressed in traditional costumes and on horseback, to pick up the flag and carry it in a kind of procession preceded by drummers from La Alberca to the hermitage of San Blas, where it is placed on top of the belfry.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'lunesdepascua', 'Before starting the procession, the quintas, also dressed in typical Alberca costumes, read the manifesto dated 7 May 1547, an ancient edict of the Duchess of Alba, which ordered the celebration to commemorate the heroic work of the women of Alberca. Once the banner has been placed on the belfry, the quintos entertain all those present with wine and hornazo. In the afternoon, the women are in charge of collecting the banner and taking it back to the town hall.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'diadeltrago', 'The Día del Trago is a deep-rooted festival in the town of La Alberca in Salamanca, where on the Monday after Easter, wine, wafers and biscuits are handed out to those who come to the town. The tradition dates back to the 15th century when the Duchess of Alba, to whom the council of La Alberca belonged, ordered that free wine be offered to the whole town in gratitude for its support in the civil war.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'diadeltrago', 'However, there are many who claim that the reason for this celebration is different; its origin would be in the water that La Alberca ceded to towns such as Monforte or Sotoserrano, that is, La Alberca allowed the rivers that carried water to these towns to flow freely, in exchange for a tax levied in wine. This could be one of the reasons why wine is served from Sotoserrano and not from other localities.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'diadeltrago', 'For others, the origin would be the sum of the two previous ones; the house of Alba, lady of La Alberca, let the water flow in exchange for wine, which was given to La Alberca in gratitude for its participation in the Castilian civil war.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'diadeltrago', 'Nowadays, it is the Town Hall who on this day invites the neighbours to "hornazo" and wine. The wine is served by the "escancianos", who are the men who have married during the last year. It is served in copper amphorae, called "galletas", and in double silver glasses known as "barquillos".');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'romeriamajadas', 'One of the traditions that has remained practically intact over the years is the Majadas Viejas pilgrimage, also known as the Maralviejas pilgrimage. According to legend, the last Visigoth king, Don Rodrigo, after losing the battle of Segoyuela de los Cornejos, had to hide in the Sierra de Francia.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'romeriamajadas', 'On his way through what is now the area around La Alberca, he hid an image of the Virgin that he always took with him to his battles. Some time later, the hermit Froilán Porqueiro found the carving in the area where the shepherds built their huts to guard their flocks, known as the Majadas Viejas. The people of Alberca took the discovery as a sign and built a hermitage in honour of the Virgin, which they called the Virgin of Majadas Viejas, and the hermitage was given the name of Ermita de las Majadas Viejas (Hermitage of Majadas Viejas).');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'romeriamajadas', 'Every year a pilgrimage is held in which the Virgin is taken in procession, followed by various celebrations. These include traditional dances and a sacramental loa performed in the place where the carving was found, ending the day with the release of heifers and a verbena for the enjoyment of the people. All of this takes place in the middle of a magnificent oak grove located about 3 km from La Alberca, where the hermitage is situated. Originally, it was held on the day of Pentecost, but nowadays it is moved to the previous Saturday, for the enjoyment of the people of La Alberca and all visitors.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'diagosto', 'At mid-morning on 15 August, municipal authorities, members of the brotherhoods and dancers gather in the main square and, together with the drummers who have just arrived from the parade announcing the big day, head towards the church to celebrate the Eucharist in honour of the patron saint of the village: Our Lady the Virgin of the Assumption.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'diagosto', 'After mass, the statue of the Virgin of the Assumption is carried in procession to the main square through streets decorated with quilts, cloths and flowers for the celebration, accompanied by the authorities, the townspeople and the drummers and dancers playing and dancing around it.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'diagosto', 'Once the image has been placed in the upper part of the square, the Offertory begins: a ritual with a very strict and solemn order, in which first the authorities and stewards, dressed in traditional costume, kneel three times in three specific places before the Patron Saint, never turning their backs to her.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'diagosto', 'In the same way, the families of the Mayordomos make the same offering; each family leaves from one of the four corners of the Plaza, and in strict order of kinship, the relatives of the Mayordomo offer the Virgin different gifts: candles, quilts, clothes, money... ');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'diagosto', 'Lastly, the dancers. After making their offering to the Virgin, they dance the cross, the corro, the paloteos (commemorations of ancient war dances), and weave and unweave the bouquet. This is one of the most beautiful days to see the costumes of La Alberca, and the spectacular "Traje de Vistas", worn by the Mayordomas and the brides on their wedding day.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'corpus', 'Corpus Christi is another of the festivities in La Alberca where the beautiful traditional architecture of this village shines with its own light. It is a great opportunity to see old traditional embroidery from the mountains, as the town dresses up for the festivity.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'corpus', 'Cloths on top and thyme on the ground, colour and aroma. This is how the streets through which the procession with the monstrance of the Holy Sacrament passes are decorated. The locals are busy decorating or polishing balconies and windows with bedspreads, shawls, etc., all hand-woven on old looms and displaying beautiful embroidery from the mountains. A black crepe on the embroidered cloth or quilt indicates that the family is in mourning. The route is punctuated by various altars, beautifully decorated with tablecloths, flowers and images of the Infant Jesus.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'corpus', 'The first altar is in the main square. This is where the municipal authorities carry the canopy, where it is handed over to the stewards. They will carry it for the rest of the procession. In the atrium of the church, the Solano Bajero, the offertory is celebrated with great solemnity. Stewards and confreres, dressed in sober cloaks, kneel three times without turning their backs to the Blessed Sacrament. The children who have received their first communion that year throw rose petals as the monstrance is raised.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'cristodelsudor', 'The festival of the Santísimo Cristo del Sudor is a traditional celebration in La Alberca that always takes place on a Sunday in May, although the date is not fixed. The origin of the festivity dates back to 1 September 1665, when a pilgrim who was walking towards the Peña de Francia saw how the Christ was sweating blood. The next day, they saw that the blood was coming out of his side.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'cristodelsudor', 'Since that event, the town of La Alberca has been devoted to its veneration, and in 1685 the Brotherhood of the Holy Christ of the Sweat was founded. This brotherhood is made up of only men: the Abbot, 33 brothers in memory of the years that Christ lived, and the aspiring brothers, who number more than a hundred.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'cristodelsudor', 'This traditional confraternity has several missions of vital importance, such as the veneration of the image, the celebration of its feast day and the presidency of the procession of the Holy Burial on the Friday of Sorrow, in which the confreres march dressed in their cloaks and their wide-brimmed black hats, carrying lighted axes. On the other hand, when one of the members of the brotherhood dies, the rest of the members of the brotherhood accompany him in the burial.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'cristodelsudor', 'On the day of the festival, all the members of the brotherhood, accompanied by the stewards, go to the house of the Abbot so that they can all go together to the celebration of the Holy Mass, where each member must carry a candle that is lit during the mass. Throughout the day they take turns to keep watch over Christ. ');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'cristodelsudor', 'In the afternoon they meet again for the rosary, where the Relic of the Holy Thorn is venerated. Once the rosary is over, the relic is passed to the faithful to kiss. It is a very moving moment, as the relic, which is strongly guarded, was donated by a Dominican monk and comes from the crown of the Lord, according to the certificate of authenticity issued from Rome in recognition of the miracle that took place in La Alberca in 1665.');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'cristodelsudor', 'Afterwards, the members of the brotherhood accompany the Abbot back to his house led by the drummer. On arrival, it is traditional for the Abbot to distribute to each brother three quartos of wine in old silver cups called barquillos and three famous bizcochos de suela, so called because they must be at least the size of the foot of the Abbot. ');
INSERT INTO fiesta (idioma, nombreFiesta, descrFiesta) VALUES ('en', 'cristodelsudor', 'After the feast, the offices of the brotherhood are renewed, being curious that each year the office of Abbot rotates and that they can only hold the office once in their lifetime. At this event, it is also decided whether or not to approve the entry of new aspiring members of the brotherhood.');